translated: Jansson, Gustav Waldemar, agronomist, Skövde, born on May 8, 1898 in Köping to Bror Axel J. and Edla Sofia Persson. Married on November 30 to Elsa Knutsson. Children: Birgitta, born in 1931. Graduated from Ultuna Agricultural Institute in Uppsala in 1924. Worked as a farm bookkeeper at Stäflö estate in Läckeby from 1925 to 1928, farm manager at Törnerum estate in Rockneby from 1928 to 1940, and farm manager at Stäringe estate in Vadsbro from 1940 to 1943. Employed at the national wool authority in Stockholm from 1943 to 1944, district manager at A-B Bolinder-Munktell in Eskilstuna in 1944. Currently working in Västergötland, Bohuslän, and Dalsland. Chairman of the Central Contracting Association in South Kalmar from 1938 to 1940, auditor at Rockneby Savings Bank from 1937 to 1940, school treasurer for Ardala school from 1941 to 1943, auditor for family aid funds in Ardala and Forssa municipality. Member of the board for Skövde Motor Club since 1946. Wrote: Travel report from study trips (1935). Hobbies: sport fishing and skiing.
